From d1dafa7cfd9fd741301755a7d083822a350cfba8 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ganesh Kariganuru Mahabalesh <gkarigan@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Wed, 27 Aug 2025 15:22:44 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] QSDK:mac80211:CP:avoid unnecessary reassignment of sdata in
 drv_sta_set_4addr()

Currently, drv_sta_set_4addr() reassigns the sdata pointer for AP_VLAN
interfaces using get_bss_sdata(), which retrieves the parent sdata.
This reassignment can prevent the driver from accessing the AP_VLAN
interface correctly.

Add a conditional check to skip get_bss_sdata() when the hardware supports
IEEE80211_HW_SUPPORTS_VLAN_DATA_OFFLOAD. This ensures that APIs involving
AP_VLAN interfaces reach the driver

Patch-dependency:
	0239-QSDK-mac80211-Add-support-to-notify-AP_VLAN-related-.patch

Signed-off-by: Ganesh Kariganuru Mahabalesh <gkarigan@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
 net/mac80211/driver-ops.h | 4 +++-
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/net/mac80211/driver-ops.h b/net/mac80211/driver-ops.h
index 1889fbb..06a13ca 100644
--- a/net/mac80211/driver-ops.h
+++ b/net/mac80211/driver-ops.h
@@ -1625,7 +1625,9 @@ static inline void drv_sta_set_4addr(struct ieee80211_local *local,
 				     struct ieee80211_sub_if_data *sdata,
 				     struct ieee80211_sta *sta, bool enabled)
 {
-	sdata = get_bss_sdata(sdata);
+	if (!ieee80211_hw_check(&local->hw, SUPPORTS_NSS_OFFLOAD) &&
+	    !ieee80211_hw_check(&local->hw, SUPPORTS_VLAN_DATA_OFFLOAD))
+		sdata = get_bss_sdata(sdata);
 
 	might_sleep();
 	lockdep_assert_wiphy(local->hw.wiphy);
-- 
